Object.Field: LKM File to Oracle OLH-OSCH Direct
SNP_TRT : LKM File to Oracle OLH-OSCH

COMPONENT NAME: LKM File to Oracle OLH-OSCH Direct COMPONENT VERSION: 1 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 12.1.3.0.1 and above DESCRIPTION: This KM integrates data from an HDFS file into an Oracle target using Oracle Loader for Hadoop (OLH) and/or Oracle SQL Connector for Hadoop (OSCH) The KM can handle filename wildcards (*, ?). This is a direct load LKM (no staging) and must be used without any IKM. Additional information can be found on KM option descriptions.
Please see BigDataConnector Documentation for more details.

Check this option, if you wish to create the target table. Default: false In case of USE_STAGING_TABLE = false, please note that data will only be read correctly, if the target table definition, particularly the row format and file format details, are correct.
String opt = options.getValue("OLH_OUTPUT_MODE"); if (opt.equals("JDBC")) return "show=true,enable=true"; if (opt.equals("OCI")) return "show=true,enable=true"; return "show=true,enable=false";

Set this option to true, if you wish to replace any existing target table content with the new data. For Hive and HBase targets the target table will be truncated. For File targets the target directory will be removed. For file targets this option must be set to true.
String opt = options.getValue("OLH_OUTPUT_MODE"); if (opt.equals("JDBC")) return "show=true,enable=true"; if (opt.equals("OCI")) return "show=true,enable=true"; return "show=true,enable=false";
Set this option to true, if you wish to replace the target table content with the new data.
